The paper proposes a method for pruning recurrent neural networks (RNNs) to reduce their size and computational burden, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper focuses on language modeling and machine reading comprehension tasks, which are typically associated with natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
